26namespace webrtc {

28// This proxy is passed to the underlying media engine to receive audio data as
29// they come in. The data will then be passed back up to the RemoteAudioSource
30// which will fan it out to all the sinks that have been added to it.
31class RemoteAudioSource::AudioDataProxy : public AudioSinkInterface {
32 public:
33 explicit AudioDataProxy(RemoteAudioSource* source) : source_(source) {
34 RTC_DCHECK(source);
35 }
36
37 AudioDataProxy() = delete;
38 AudioDataProxy(const AudioDataProxy&) = delete;
39 AudioDataProxy& operator=(const AudioDataProxy&) = delete;
40
41 ~AudioDataProxy() override { source_->OnAudioChannelGone(); }
42
43 // AudioSinkInterface implementation.
44 void OnData(const AudioSinkInterface::Data& audio) override {
45 source_->OnData(audio);
46 }
47
48 private:
49 const rtc::scoped_refptr<RemoteAudioSource> source_;
50};
51
52RemoteAudioSource::RemoteAudioSource(
53 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
54 OnAudioChannelGoneAction on_audio_channel_gone_action)
55 : main_thread_(rtc::Thread::Current()),
56 worker_thread_(worker_thread),
57 on_audio_channel_gone_action_(on_audio_channel_gone_action),
58 state_(MediaSourceInterface::kLive) {
59 RTC_DCHECK(main_thread_);
60 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_);
61}
62
63RemoteAudioSource::~RemoteAudioSource() {
64 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
65 RTC_DCHECK(audio_observers_.empty());
66 if (!sinks_.empty()) {
67 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
68 << "RemoteAudioSource destroyed while sinks_ is non-empty.";
69 }
70}
71
72void RemoteAudioSource::Start(cricket::VoiceMediaChannel* media_channel,
73 absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc) {
74 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
75
76 // Register for callbacks immediately before AddSink so that we always get
77 // notified when a channel goes out of scope (signaled when "AudioDataProxy"
78 // is destroyed).
79 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel);
80 ssrc ? media_channel->SetRawAudioSink(*ssrc,
81 std::make_unique<AudioDataProxy>(this))
82 : media_channel->SetDefaultRawAudioSink(
83 std::make_unique<AudioDataProxy>(this));
84}
85
86void RemoteAudioSource::Stop(cricket::VoiceMediaChannel* media_channel,
87 absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc) {
88 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
89 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel);
90 ssrc ? media_channel->SetRawAudioSink(*ssrc, nullptr)
91 : media_channel->SetDefaultRawAudioSink(nullptr);
92}
93
94void RemoteAudioSource::SetState(SourceState new_state) {
95 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
96 if (state_ != new_state) {
97 state_ = new_state;
98 FireOnChanged();
99 }
100}
101
102MediaSourceInterface::SourceState RemoteAudioSource::state() const {
103 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
104 return state_;
105}
106
107bool RemoteAudioSource::remote() const {
108 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
109 return true;
110}
111
112void RemoteAudioSource::SetVolume(double volume) {
113 RTC_DCHECK_GE(volume, 0);
114 RTC_DCHECK_LE(volume, 10);
115 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << rtc::StringFormat("RAS::%s({volume=%.2f})", __func__,
116 volume);
117 for (auto* observer : audio_observers_) {
118 observer->OnSetVolume(volume);
119 }
120}
121
122void RemoteAudioSource::RegisterAudioObserver(AudioObserver* observer) {
123 RTC_DCHECK(observer != NULL);
124 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(audio_observers_, observer));
125 audio_observers_.push_back(observer);
126}
127
128void RemoteAudioSource::UnregisterAudioObserver(AudioObserver* observer) {
129 RTC_DCHECK(observer != NULL);
130 audio_observers_.remove(observer);
131}
132
133void RemoteAudioSource::AddSink(AudioTrackSinkInterface* sink) {
134 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
135 RTC_DCHECK(sink);
136
137 if (state_ != MediaSourceInterface::kLive) {
138 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can't register sink as the source isn't live.";
139 return;
140 }
141
142 MutexLock lock(&sink_lock_);
143 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(sinks_, sink));
144 sinks_.push_back(sink);
145}
146
147void RemoteAudioSource::RemoveSink(AudioTrackSinkInterface* sink) {
148 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
149 RTC_DCHECK(sink);
150
151 MutexLock lock(&sink_lock_);
152 sinks_.remove(sink);
153}
154
155void RemoteAudioSource::OnData(const AudioSinkInterface::Data& audio) {
156 // Called on the externally-owned audio callback thread, via/from webrtc.
157 MutexLock lock(&sink_lock_);
158 for (auto* sink : sinks_) {
159 // When peerconnection acts as an audio source, it should not provide
160 // absolute capture timestamp.
161 sink->OnData(audio.data, 16, audio.sample_rate, audio.channels,
162 audio.samples_per_channel,
163 /*absolute_capture_timestamp_ms=*/absl::nullopt);
164 }
165}
166
167void RemoteAudioSource::OnAudioChannelGone() {
168 if (on_audio_channel_gone_action_ != OnAudioChannelGoneAction::kEnd) {
169 return;
170 }
171 // Called when the audio channel is deleted. It may be the worker thread
172 // in libjingle or may be a different worker thread.
173 // This object needs to live long enough for the cleanup logic in OnMessage to
174 // run, so take a reference to it as the data. Sometimes the message may not
175 // be processed (because the thread was destroyed shortly after this call),
176 // but that is fine because the thread destructor will take care of destroying
177 // the message data which will release the reference on RemoteAudioSource.
178 main_thread_->Post(RTC_FROM_HERE, this, 0,
179 new rtc::ScopedRefMessageData<RemoteAudioSource>(this));
180}
181
182void RemoteAudioSource::OnMessage(rtc::Message* msg) {
183 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_thread_);
184 sinks_.clear();
185 SetState(MediaSourceInterface::kEnded);
186 // Will possibly delete this RemoteAudioSource since it is reference counted
187 // in the message.
188 delete msg->pdata;
189}
